UN Secretary General Kofi Annan expressed deep concern over Nepal's democracy after King Gyanendra dismissed the government and imposed a state of emergency.
The EU and the United States also called for a swift return to democracy.
Japan urged peace through dialogue with Maoist rebels.
India aims to secure its border and maintain ties with Nepal.
China remained neutral, respecting Nepal's internal affairs.
The US faces a policy challenge due to its military aid to Nepal.
Despite international condemnation, King Gyanendra named a new Cabinet to restore democracy and end the Maoist rebellion.
Nepal's future remains uncertain amidst political turmoil.
